com.facebook.litho

Class LogEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.litho.LogEvent

  • public class LogEvent
extends Object
    A class representing an event to log to a ComponentsLogger. There are two kind of events, performance events and regular events. Performance events track the time between instantiation and being logged while regular events do not. A LogEvent is created by requesting a new event from the ComponentsLogger and they are recycled when logged and should not be re-used.
